{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:15:38.903891+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a complete summary of how to install, configure, and deploy this React Firebase Starter to GitHub Pages, based on the repository contents.\n\n---\n\n## 📦 1. Installation\n\nThis project is a **Create React App (CRA) template** published as `cra-template-firebase-starter`. Install it with:\n\n```bash\nnpx create-react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\nOr with Yarn:\n\n```bash\nyarn create react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\nThis scaffolds a React app pre-wired with:\n- **React Router** (`react-router-dom`) for client-side routing\n- **Firebase** SDK with Google Authentication\n- **Material UI** (`@mui/material`) for the login screen\n- **gh-pages** for GitHub Pages deployment\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ 2. Configuration\n\n### A. Set up Firebase\n\n1. Go to the [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/) and **create a new project**.\n2. Register a **web app** (click the web icon `</>`). Firebase will give you an SDK config object.\n3. Copy the values into the **`.env`** file at the root of your project. The template ships with placeholder values:\n\n```\nREACT_APP_FirebaseApiKey=...\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAuthDomain=...\nREACT_APP_FirebaseProjectId=...\nREACT_APP_FirebaseStorageBucket=...\nREACT_APP_FirebaseMessagingSenderId=...\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAppId=...\n```\n\nThese are read by `src/config/firebase.config.js`:\n\n```js\nexport const firebaseConfig = {\n  apiKey: process.env.REACT_APP_FirebaseApiKey,\n  authDomain: process.env.REACT_APP_FirebaseAuthDomain,\n  projectId: process.env.REACT_APP_FirebaseProjectId,\n  storageBucket: process.env.REACT_APP_FirebaseStorageBucket,\n  messagingSenderId: process.env.REACT_APP_FirebaseMessagingSenderId,\n  appId: process.env.REACT_APP_FirebaseAppId,\n};\n```\n\nAnd then initialized in `src/config/firebase.js`:\n\n```js\nimport { initializeApp } from \"firebase/app\";\nimport { firebaseConfig } from \"./firebase.config\";\nimport { getAuth, GoogleAuthProvider } from \"firebase/auth\";\n\nexport const Firebase = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);\nexport const auth = getAuth();\nexport const Providers = { google: new GoogleAuthProvider() };\n```\n\n### B. Enable Google Sign-In\n\n1. In the Firebase Console, go to **Authentication → Get Started**.\n2. In the **Sign-in method** tab, click **Google**.\n3. Toggle **Enable** and click **Save**.\n\n### C. (Optional) Adding new screens/routes\n\nCreate a new component in `src/screens/`, then register it in `src/config/routes.js`:\n\n```js\n{\n  path: \"/your-route\",\n  component: YourScreenComponentName,\n  name: \"Screen Name For Reference\",\n  protected: false, // true = requires authentication\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 3. Deploy to GitHub Pages\n\nThe template includes `gh-pages` as a dev dependency and has pre-configured npm scripts for deployment:\n\n```json\n\"predeploy\": \"npm run build\",\n\"deploy\": \"gh-pages -d build\"\n```\n\n### Steps:\n\n1. **Add your GitHub Pages domain** (e.g., `your-username.github.io`) to the **OAuth redirect domains** list in Firebase Console → Authentication → Sign-in method tab.\n\n2. **Update the `homepage` field** in `package.json` to match your deployment URL. The template defaults to:\n   ```json\n   \"homepage\": \"http://pettiboy.github.com/cra-template-firebase-starter\"\n   ```\n   Change it to your own:\n   ```json\n   \"homepage\": \"http://your-username.github.io/your-repo-name\"\n   ```\n\n3. **(Optional) Test the production build locally:**\n   ```bash\n   # Set homepage to \"/\" temporarily, then:\n   npm i -g serve\n   npm run build-and-serve\n   ```\n\n4. **Deploy:**\n   ```bash\n   npm run deploy\n   ```\n   This runs `npm run build` (via `predeploy`) and then pushes the `build/` directory to a `gh-pages` branch.\n\nThe project also uses [`spa-github-pages`](https://github.com/rafgraph/spa-github-pages) to handle client-side routing on GitHub Pages (which doesn't natively support SPAs), ensuring React Router paths work correctly on refresh.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 970, "prompt_tokens": 8134, "total_tokens": 9104, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 16, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7872, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0009862092, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001423092, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0008439}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863322-z9ty5Kjn2eesT01y5jsL", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b9-c9f7-7521-8367-996e822550d4-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8134, "output_tokens": 970, "total_tokens": 9104, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7872}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 16}}}}]}}}
